&gt; 
&gt; Domain objects support the GUI. By the logic above a well 
&gt; tested GUI will include the behavior of the domain objects, 
&gt; so there is no reason to unit test the domain objects :-)
&gt; 
&gt; I&#39;ve occasionally found reason to write unit tests for 
&gt; private, supporting methods. Often you loose efficiency 
&gt; testing supporting methods indirectly via their caller - such 
&gt; as in the case where you want to test their ability to 
&gt; properly handle a range of input values. 
&gt; 
&gt; Personally, I don&#39;t believe in private methods. I&#39;d rather 
&gt; make everything public and testable and expose real APIs via 
&gt; Java Interfaces.
